ZIKA VIRUS - COLOMBIA (06)
**************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

In this update:
National
San Andres department
Santander department
Risaralda department
Ibague, Tolima department

******
National. 11 Nov 2015. (susp.) 486 cases with 185 in the city of Cartagena, (conf.) 341 cases. Departments most affected: Bolivar 81 cases, Antioquia 47 cases, Norte de Santander 44 cases, San Andres 37 cases, Risaralda 18 cases. Ministry of Health indicates 26 million Colombians at risk of infection.
http://www.elespectador.com/noticias/nacional/ya-son-mas-de-340-los-casos-de-contagiados-virus-zika-c-articulo-598544 [in Spanish]

San Andres Department. 11 Nov 2015. (reported) about 32 cases.
http://www.rcnradio.com/locales/en-san-andres-se-confirman-32-casos-del-virus-zika/ [in Spanish]

Santander Department. 11 Nov 2015. (conf.) 9 cases. Municipalities with cases: Bucaramanga 5 cases, Lebrija 4 cases.
http://www.wradio.com.co/noticias/regionales/8203santander-confirman-nueve-casos-del-virus-zika/20151111/nota/2995037.aspx [in Spanish]

Risaralda Department. 9 Nov 2015. (conf.) 8 cases. Municipalities affected: Pereira 6 cases, Dosquebradas 1 case, Balboa 1 case.
http://www.elespectador.com/noticias/nacional/confirman-ocho-casos-del-virus-zika-risaralda-articulo-598100 [in Spanish]

Ibague, Tolima department. 9 Nov 2015. (conf.) 1st case.
http://hsbnoticias.com/noticias/nacional/alerta-en-ibague-tras-confirmacion-del-primer-caso-del-virus-168390 [in Spanish]

